      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BETTORLEFTALONE (2) led as a hot favourite when resuming at Menangle and while he couldn't see it out he boxed on and finished 4 metres away in third. That was his first outing for five months so it will have improved him and he should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Can atone. WINGMAN LOU (8) produced a very good effort in a higher-graded race last time at Bathurst, finishing third and just 1.2 metres from the winner. Draws on the second line but is a three-time winner at this venue. MEANT TO BE SLOY (3) last appeared ten weeks ago but has been readied with three trials. Strikes at 50 per cent at this circuit and distance and has a win and a placing from two previous fresh attempts. ALLORNOTHINGLEVI (1) should get every chance from the ace draw.",
